ANNE MCELVOY SPEAKS to two candidates in the race to succeed Theresa May as Conservative leader and Britain's prime minister. She catches up with Rory Stewart, the international development secretary, who proposes a “citizens’ assembly” to solve Brexit. And she asks the foreign secretary, Jeremy Hunt, how he would avoid a no-deal Brexit and how he explained the National Health Service to President Donald Trump. Runtime: 36 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn